ken with only one side of surface mount resistor left on board. Scavenged an R33 1R00, 1 ohm resistor off an old/bad board and installed on 0024 serial board. Inspected serial board, but did not find any corrosion on it.'), (@con_inst_id,'2019-02-21 00:00:00','FOUND SOME CORROSION ON CONNECTOR BOARD, SO INSTALLED NEW CONNECTOR BOARD.'), (@con_inst_id,'2019-02-21 00:00:00','Installed new GPS antenna/cable and new iridium antenna cable, new Hubbell rubber plugs and a new Iridium/GPS antenna housing O-ring.'), (@con_inst_id,'2019-02-22 00:00:00','Installed NEW face and jam seal O-rings.'), (@con_inst_id,'2019-02-25 00:00:00','Ran Current drain BENCH test for 3 days, 13.26mA Average. Dumped FLASH RAM data file, which looked okay.'), (@con_inst_id,'2019-02-25 00:00:00','Successfully tested GPS and XMIT commands outside on internal antennas.'), (@con_inst_id,'2019-02-25 00:00:00','WAITING TO INSTALL NEW potted RF modem antenna from TIM.'), (@con_inst_id,'2019-02-25 00:00:00','DON\'T FORGET TO SEAL THE INSIDE RF ANTENNA HOLE WITH RTV. SHOULD NOW DO FOR ALL SYSTEMS.');
